snippet.title: SNES Super Tennis
snippet.description:
This game was on the SNES European launch lineup.

Most people tend not to notice, but theres one really amazing thing about this game: The sound.

It was for the first game to ever had such accurate and realistic tennis sound effects, something that we take for granted today, it was quite amazing back then, and showed off the SPC700 capabilities.

up to this day, a really addictive and solid tennis game, especialy fun in multiplayer, a truly worthy sequel to the NES Tennis original. Mario keept his job as a referee, too.
